      <h1 class='title'>Criminal Injuries Compensation Appeals Panel Northern Ireland: Corporate and Business Plans</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 20 December 2004 vol 667 c110WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_110ws' title='Col. 110WS &mdash; HL Deb 20 December 2004 vol 667 c110WS' name='column_110ws' href='#column_110ws' rel='bookmark'>110WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0667P0-09278'>
        <a name='S5LV0667P0_20041220_LWS_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-valerie-amos' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041220_LWS_7' title='Link to this speech by Ms Valerie Amos' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-valerie-amos" title="Ms Valerie Amos">Baroness Amos</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0667P0-09278">My right honourable friend the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland has made the following Ministerial Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0667P0-09279">I have today received from the Criminal Injuries Compensation Appeals Panel Northern Ireland copies of the corporate plan for the period 2004&#x2013;07 and the business plan for the financial year 2004&#x2013;05. The corporate plan outlines the panel's aims, objectives and responsibilities for the period 2004&#x2013;07 and the business plan its targets and objectives in the financial year 2004&#x2013;05. Copies of the plans have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
